questions.prompt:
A PiggyVest savings script has the following data. Write four console calls: (1) console.log with a label showing the user's name and balance; (2) console.warn if the balance is below minBalance; (3) console.error if the accountName is an empty string; (4) console.table showing the transactions array.

```js
const accountName  = "Ngozi Eze";
const balance      = 4200;
const minBalance   = 5000;
const transactions = [
  { date: "2025-04-01", amount: 3000,  type: "deposit"    },
  { date: "2025-04-08", amount: -1500, type: "withdrawal" },
  { date: "2025-04-15", amount: 2700,  type: "deposit"    }
];
```

questions.expected_answer:
console.log("Account:", accountName, "| Balance: ₦", balance);
console.warn("Balance below minimum — current:", balance, "min:", minBalance);
// console.error is NOT triggered because accountName is not empty
// If accountName were "": console.error("Account name cannot be empty!");
console.table(transactions);

// Key points: balance (4200) < minBalance (5000) so warn fires;
// accountName is not empty so error does NOT fire (or student may add an if check);
// console.table receives the transactions array

