A student is debugging a loop that calculates total sales for a Chowdeck delivery record. They want to add console.log calls to see what is happening at each step. Write the console.log statements they should add: one before the loop (showing the starting total), and one inside the loop (showing the current index, the current order value, and the running total after each addition).

```js
const orders = [3200, 1800, 4500, 900, 2700];
let salesTotal = 0;

for (let i = 0; i < orders.length; i++) {
  salesTotal = salesTotal + orders[i];
}

console.log("Final total: ₦", salesTotal);
```

questions.expected_answer:
// Before the loop:
console.log("Starting total:", salesTotal);

// Inside the loop (after the addition):
for (let i = 0; i < orders.length; i++) {
  salesTotal = salesTotal + orders[i];
  console.log("Iteration:", i, "| Added: ₦", orders[i], "| Running total: ₦", salesTotal);
