questions.prompt:
The following Cowry Budget script has two bugs — one ReferenceError and one TypeError. Find both bugs, identify each error type, and write the corrected script.

```js
const userName    = "Bayo Adeyemi";
const monthlyIncome = 285000;
const savingsGoal   = 60000;

console.log("User:", username);
console.log("Income: ₦", monthlyIncome);

const goalPercent = savingsGoal.slice(0, 3);
console.log("Goal (first 3 chars):", goalPercent);
```

questions.expected_answer:
Bug 1 — ReferenceError on line 5:
'username' should be 'userName' (capital N).
console.log("User:", userName);

Bug 2 — TypeError on line 8:
'savingsGoal' is a number (60000). Numbers do not have a .slice() method — that is a string method.
Fix: either convert to string first, or simply log the number directly.
const goalPercent = String(savingsGoal).slice(0, 3); // produces "600"
// OR: just remove the .slice() call and log savingsGoal directly

Full corrected script:
const userName      = "Bayo Adeyemi";
const monthlyIncome = 285000;
const savingsGoal   = 60000;

console.log("User:", userName);
console.log("Income: ₦", monthlyIncome);

const goalPrefix = String(savingsGoal).slice(0, 3);
console.log("Goal prefix:", goalPrefix);

